      <Content>There are two basic problems involved in the translation of {S:05000201000026}. For example, the phrase ‘at the name of Jesus’ may mean ‘when the name of Jesus is proclaimed’ or ‘when the presence of Jesus is announced.’ The phrase ‘every knee’ means every person, since ‘knee’ is a figurative substitute for a person (see {D:9.16}).</Content>
